    {
      "id": "x7lXBBGTwvChfwutUblaU",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -304.18644987761184,
      "y": -196.80248443647002,
      "width": 770,
      "height": 1025,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0V",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 907219755,
      "version": 3090,
      "versionNonce": 762156661,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774977921514,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Timer: Delay (hours, minutes, seconds), URL\nWebhook: Call `sendcloud.com/api/start` when Timer expires\n\n\nFunctional Requirements:\n— Create a Timer\n— Get Timer status (`time_left`)\n— Fire Webhook when Timer expires\n\nOut of Scope:\n— DAG\n— Recurring Timers/Jobs\n— Execution Tracking\n— RBAC / Users\n— CronJob\n\nScale:\n— High-traffic ~ 100 RPS\n— Horizontal Scaling\n— Support multi-server deployment\n\n\nNon-Functional Requirements:\n— Handle invalid input\n— Survive process restarts\n— Fire expired Timers after recovery\n— Each Timer fires only once\n\n\nAssumption:\n— Availability > Consistency\n— Latency call url within a second\n— Scalability to 10k timer/s\n— Exact-Once[X] Execution\n— Webhook failures [500x, Network, I/O] may be retried (design choice)\n\n\nCore Entities:\n— Timer\n— Execution\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Timer: Delay (hours, minutes, seconds), URL\nWebhook: Call `sendcloud.com/api/start` when Timer expires\n\n\nFunctional Requirements:\n— Create a Timer\n— Get Timer status (`time_left`)\n— Fire Webhook when Timer expires\n\nOut of Scope:\n— DAG\n— Recurring Timers/Jobs\n— Execution Tracking\n— RBAC / Users\n— CronJob\n\nScale:\n— High-traffic ~ 100 RPS\n— Horizontal Scaling\n— Support multi-server deployment\n\n\nNon-Functional Requirements:\n— Handle invalid input\n— Survive process restarts\n— Fire expired Timers after recovery\n— Each Timer fires only once\n\n\nAssumption:\n— Availability > Consistency\n— Latency call url within a second\n— Scalability to 10k timer/s\n— Exact-Once[X] Execution\n— Webhook failures [500x, Network, I/O] may be retried (design choice)\n\n\nCore Entities:\n— Timer\n— Execution\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "kFs8Wfwv3zm_pySLGIbEY",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 684.7049734878111,
      "y": -198.6892562221259,
      "width": 627,
      "height": 900,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0d",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1337213061,
      "version": 630,
      "versionNonce": 689829003,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774904174656,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "API\n\n// create a timer\nPOST /timers → Timer\n{\n    \"hours\": 4,\n    \"minutes\": 0,\n    \"seconds\": 1,\n    \"url\": \"https://someserver.com\"\n}\n\nResponse\n{\n\"id\": \"be18064e-d265-4cb5-9716-34f249029a79\",\n\"time_left\": 14401\n}\n\n\n// get a timer\nGET /timers/{timer_uuid}\n{\n\"id\" : \"be18064e-d265-4cb5-9716-34f249029a79\",\n\"time_left\": 645\n}\n\n\n\nData Flow\n\n1. User create a timer\n2. Persist the timer in DB\n3. Execute Webhook when Timer expires → How?\n    — If failure, retry with exponential backoff + jitter\n4. Update the timer status -> fired\n5. On restart, recover and fire missed expired Timers\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "API\n\n// create a timer\nPOST /timers → Timer\n{\n    \"hours\": 4,\n    \"minutes\": 0,\n    \"seconds\": 1,\n    \"url\": \"https://someserver.com\"\n}\n\nResponse\n{\n\"id\": \"be18064e-d265-4cb5-9716-34f249029a79\",\n\"time_left\": 14401\n}\n\n\n// get a timer\nGET /timers/{timer_uuid}\n{\n\"id\" : \"be18064e-d265-4cb5-9716-34f249029a79\",\n\"time_left\": 645\n}\n\n\n\nData Flow\n\n1. User create a timer\n2. Persist the timer in DB\n3. Execute Webhook when Timer expires → How?\n    — If failure, retry with exponential backoff + jitter\n4. Update the timer status -> fired\n5. On restart, recover and fire missed expired Timers\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "pSk2dgEK9aBbWEBFJoSKm",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -137.99520701821916,
      "y": -862.4232620035912,
      "width": 1530.934750932351,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0k",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 97982443,
      "version": 500,
      "versionNonce": 1546151845,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774898368363,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\nA scheduled task service is a web service that lets users create a timer by providing a URL and a delay in hours, minutes, and seconds.\nWhen the timer expires, the service calls the given URL. It also lets users query how much time is left for a timer.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\nA scheduled task service is a web service that lets users create a timer by providing a URL and a delay in hours, minutes, and seconds.\nWhen the timer expires, the service calls the given URL. It also lets users query how much time is left for a timer.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
