    },
    {
      "id": "F7kisFx7sL-SYcJBzZygD",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3734.1991454905005,
      "y": -282.78218062547046,
      "width": 950.398681640625,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "uv3fBkORV9kDwnwHNBc5N"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3Dh",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1037464363,
      "version": 1672,
      "versionNonce": 135258667,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774906351528,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "ATTENTION:\nIf I query timers that needed to execute in the next 5m and put them on MSQ\nMeanwhile a User `create 00:01:00, URL` -> right on the Queue, fine!\nBut many MSQ are Log-based and ordered (FIFO) like Kafka Append-Only-Log-File | Disk Based\nSo I can not reprioritize it 5\nFinally `create 00:01:00, URL` -> will execute in 5m or 5m and couple of second\n\n\n\nWe need Something in memory operate as priority queue or as heap\n\n- Redis Sorted Set -> heapify -> timer will put to right spot\nIf so we need read replicas and Sentinel high availability mode, one master 2 replica, auto failover and ...\n\n- RabbitMQ: provide this delayed message exhange\nis not typically trusted as heavily for production systems\n\n- SQS: has delivery delay up to 15 meniutes can handle heapification\nmakes RETRIES a lot easier. support DLQs. High Availability\n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "ATTENTION:\nIf I query timers that needed to execute in the next 5m and put them on MSQ\nMeanwhile a User `create 00:01:00, URL` -> right on the Queue, fine!\nBut many MSQ are Log-based and ordered (FIFO) like Kafka Append-Only-Log-File | Disk Based\nSo I can not reprioritize it 5\nFinally `create 00:01:00, URL` -> will execute in 5m or 5m and couple of second\n\n\n\nWe need Something in memory operate as priority queue or as heap\n\n- Redis Sorted Set -> heapify -> timer will put to right spot\nIf so we need read replicas and Sentinel high availability mode, one master 2 replica, auto failover and ...\n\n- RabbitMQ: provide this delayed message exhange\nis not typically trusted as heavily for production systems\n\n- SQS: has delivery delay up to 15 meniutes can handle heapification\nmakes RETRIES a lot easier. support DLQs. High Availability\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
